LEGISLATION: Provides for required disclosures on local notices
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To adopt House Rule 7.20 of the Rules of Order of the House of Representatives, relative
3 to notice of intent to introduce a bill to enact a local or special law; to provide for
4 disclosure of the name of the person who caused a notice to be published if a
5 legislator is not responsible for the notice.
6 BE IT RESOLVED by the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana
7 that House Rule 7.20 of the Rules of Order of the House of Representatives is hereby
8 adopted to read as follows:
9 Rule 7.20. Required disclosure on certain notices of local or special laws
10 A notice of the intent to introduce a bill to enact a local or special law as
11 required by Article III, Section 13(A) of the Constitution of Louisiana that is caused
12 to be published by a person other than a member of the legislature shall include the
13 name of the person who caused the notice to be published.
