HR 244 Original 2026 Regular Session Bayham
Abstract: Requires the notice for a local or special law caused to be published by a person
other than a member of the legislature to include the name of the person who caused
the notice to be published.
Present constitution (Const. Art. III, Section 13(A)) provides that no local or special law
shall be enacted unless notice of the intent to introduce a bill to enact such a law has been
published on two separate days, without cost to the state, in the official journal of the locality
